<div id="review_2612752766" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2612752766" />
    <a title="Richard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8386404-richard"><img alt="Richard" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1351707681p2/8386404.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2612752766?book_show_action=true">Mar 29, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Richard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Richard" href="/user/show/8386404-richard">Richard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/34535733-summer-of-night">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8386404-richard?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8386404-richard?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8386404-richard?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2612752766" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10118088178647606110">9/10<br/><br/><b>My 500th book since records began (i.e. Goodreads)</b><br/><br/>I was totally unaware of this little beast until I read <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2605674103?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1' rel='nofollow noopener'> Dan’s great review</a> that lured me in and it was everything he said and more. What a little treat for my earbuds! <br/><br/>I’m drawn to these coming of age tales set in a time long before I was born in a land across the pond. Something about the innocence of youth in a time which, on the surface, seems simpler than life today. This is one of those stories but added in to it is a dormant horror ele</span>
  <span id="freeText10118088178647606110" style="display:none">9/10<br /><br /><b>My 500th book since records began (i.e. Goodreads)</b><br /><br />I was totally unaware of this little beast until I read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2605674103?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1" rel="nofollow noopener"> Dan’s great review</a> that lured me in and it was everything he said and more. What a little treat for my earbuds! <br /><br />I’m drawn to these coming of age tales set in a time long before I was born in a land across the pond. Something about the innocence of youth in a time which, on the surface, seems simpler than life today. This is one of those stories but added in to it is a dormant horror element on a small rural town which suddenly decides to be no longer dormant. There is a large cast of characters fleshing out this local community and it did take a bit of time to remember who was who but it soon slotted in like a 1000 piece jigsaw. <br /><br />I did this in audiobook and it was by far the longest audiobook I’ve ever listened to coming in at over 22 hours and the narrator was decent enough but there was only one speed so when something tense was happening it was confusing at first as the pace was the same as if he was describing a sandwich. That aside this was great in audio mainly down to how good the story was. I went out of my way to listen to it which says a lot. My commute would become slightly longer or I would pray to the traffic gods. <br /><br />Don’t take my review as a measuring stick for this. Check out Dan’s review and give it a try. I’d not heard of it prior to that but I’m sure glad I made the effort to hunt it down once I had!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10118088178647606110" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


